- The main benefits of wireless HDMI revolve around convenience and lack of clutter
### Go wireless.

- It's safe to say we'd all like to get rid of some of the wires around our homes and especially around the backs of our TV's. This is what wireless HDMI enables you to do. It's even more essential if you have a wall mounted TV.
- When your source is in a different location.
- Whether you want to stream Netflix in the bedroom to a TV in the living room, or connect a projector in your office boardroom, you can. There's no need to have the devices alongside each other, and no need to run long lengths of cable to connect them.
- Your TV ran out of HDMI ports.
- Most TV's have at least 2 HDMI ports, but that isn't always enough. The good news is that some wireless HDMI receivers have multiple input ports, we can easily connect the extra sources for you and stream to multiple TV's.
### Work Place Applications.

- There are many applications for the work place, from outputting a presentation from your laptop to conference room TV, to installing digital signage in your shop window.
